25 - 37

* Minimum Bit length needs to be 4

* If the most significant bit (MSB, furthest left number in answer) is 0, then the number is positive and if it is 1 then the number is negative

-8 to 7 = 4 bits
-16 to 15 5 bits <-- -9 -5 and -14
-32 to 31 6 bits
-64 to 63 7 bits <-- 25 and 37 fit in here so I use 7 bits
-128 to 127 8 bits <-- 67 and 32 and 35

