"Add the following signed binary numbers"
OVER FLOW MAY HAPPEN IF U ARE ADDING SAME SIGNED NUMBERS
Overflow: will never occur if we are adding oppositely signed numbers
to fix the overflow, a bitfield extension is needed to extend the length of the positive number. To extend a postive number, pad up 0's on the left. To extend the bit length of a negative number pad up 1's on the left

